title: Grateful Dead Live at Augusta Civic Center on 1984-10-12
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, It Must Have Been The Roses, On The Road Again, Jack A Roe, It's All Over Now, Cumberland Blues, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Cold Rain & Snow, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Don't Need Love-> Uncle John's Band-> Drums-> Playin' Reprise-> Uncle John's Band-> Morning Dew, E: Good Lovin'

Final / last "On The Road Again"

reviews.review_text: mesmerizing show this is one of the very few shows i've recently listened to that keeps one's mind and interest engaged ALL the way through... jerry's really 'on' -- as is bob. set 2 is terrific and the morning dew cranks. yes, some anomalies w/ this sbd source but hardly an issue. was at lewiston, oxford plains and portland '82 -- and maine shows just never disappoint.

Raw Jerry  This show has one of my favorite Cold Rain & Snows & Morning Dews. Because jerry has so much emotion in both songs, just beautiful. Also Bobby does a on the road again that sadly stopped being played. just such a great dead song that fit the band so well. 84' the least representative year by the current archivist for GDP, yet one of my personal favorite years.

Recordings flaws? this one seems best? I had the one where AUD was key part of the basic "tape" years of listening and there was a "shift" somewhere in Playin or UJB... around there. When I was fortunate enough to download from etree (not quite 20+ years ago), another piece came around (just Dew, I think), and I merged them for my own (wav file) versions... Anyway, to my unrefined ears, this one seems most consistent! Thanks for all y'all's work
Personal favorite show and long term tape, prior to all these vast technological improvements. 
Its almost like the Singularity Is Here!
Its not, but its like that!!!
